# Title: Visual Studio NodejsTools PressAnyKey Renamed Execution
# Author: Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems), Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)
# Date: 2023-04-11
# Level: medium
# Description: Detects renamed execution of "Microsoft.NodejsTools.PressAnyKey.exe", which can be abused as a LOLBIN to execute arbitrary binaries
# MITRE Tactic: Execution
# Tags: attack.execution, attack.stealth, attack.t1218
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_renamed_pressanykey.yml

OriginalFileName="Microsoft.NodejsTools.PressAnyKey.exe" NOT Image="*\\Microsoft.NodejsTools.PressAnyKey.exe"